5:
As I have just outlined, the
Doomsday Lances are a threat to
my people—the humans and
beastfolk of Excelion.
7:
Therefore, my forces will participate
in the mission to seize the
Doomsday Spire, along with the
fiends and Champion Light.
10:
Your "forces?" Hah! Know your place,
human!
12:
If Lord Adjudicus hadn't been with
you, we would've killed you
surface-goers ourselves.
16:
My guests. And they WILL be treated
accordingly.
19:
But why, Milord?! I can understand
the elf, but...
20:
The surface-goers are the ones who
trapped our people in this prison of
a world!
21:
Why would you side with the Purger,
the so-called "Champion"
responsible for our forefathers'
curse?!
23:
Do not attempt to use the curse as
leverage with ME.
26:
I understand your reservations, but I
urge you to consider the bigger
picture.
28:
You all swore to topple the Dark
Throne—for our survival and our
future.
30:
You have long endured this cursed,
poisoned land. You know how to grit
your teeth and use anything you
can to get ahead.
34:
We work towards a common goal:
that of peace and safety. Let us then
work together.
38:
Indeed. Lilith Stratos, I approve your
proposal.
40:
However, your "forces" can hardly be
considered an army. What do you
bring to this alliance?
49:
Yes, the Mark of Rustamov, which
you sought to take from the Silver
Woods.
51:
While this power was intended for
the Champion's use, Estariel
believed it capable of warding the
entirety of the Silver Woods.
53:
It contains a great deal of mana,
which, if employed correctly...
57:
...Could be the weapon we need to
seize the future.
63:
WE will seize our future. The mark is
merely a tool—our will and
determination are our true weapons.
67:
Whew... I got a little carried away,
there.
71:
Maybe, but a little bravado was just
what those fiends needed. You sure
didn't SOUND nervous.
76:
I know that I bring very little to this
alliance, compared to what
Adjudicus provides in both numbers
and intel.
78:
But I will do EVERYTHING in my power,
if only to make our odds the
slightest bit better.
86:
I hope you also understand that the
risks to your safety may far
outweigh the benefits.
89:
The fiends want us dead. Though
you may have convinced their
leader, you did not fully convince
the troops.
94:
I am aware of that. But while we
must exercise caution, let us do so
only when there is due cause.
96:
Please do not worry for my sake,
Light. Alk can attest to my ability to
defend myself.
99:
Besides, Adjudicus won't allow
insubordination to foil his plans. So
long as he is on our side, we need
not fear his troops.
103: You... You sound just like Princess Lily.
108:
Please forgive me for speaking out
of line, Princess.
112:
Champion! Though our use of it
may not be conventional, I fully
intend to use the Mark's power to
benefit YOUR quest.
115:
Let us reclaim our land.
...Let us reclaim our world!
118:
Of course. I swear to you, I will fulfill
my duty as Champion!
123:
Stella. Marly has likely been taken to
the Doomsday Spire.
127:
We must also make rescuing her a
priority. Together!
